titanic.train <- titanic.train %>% mutate(Embarked = case_when(Embarked== "" ~ "C",
                                                   TRUE ~ as.character(Embarked)))

Creo variable familia en dummie

titanic.train <- titanic.train %>% mutate(Familia=case_when(Parch==0 & SibSp==0 ~ 0,
                                                               TRUE ~ 1))

Genero las formulas

logit_formulas_titanic <- formulas(.response = ~Survived, # único lado derecho de las formulas.
                           edad= ~Age, 
                           clase= ~Pclass,  
                           edad_tarifa= ~Age+Fare,  
                           edad_tarifa_genero=~Age+Fare+Sex,
                           edad_sexo_clase=~Age+Pclass+Sex,
                           familia=~Familia,
                           edad_sexo_clase_familia=~Age+Pclass+Sex+Familia,
                           edad_sexo_clase_Puerto=~Age+Pclass+Sex+Embarked,
                           joven.portitulo=~joven.portitulo,
                           joven.poredad=~joven.poredad,
                           sexo_clase_puerto_jovenportit=~Sex+Pclass+joven.portitulo+Embarked,
                           genero=~Sex)

models_titanic <- data_frame(logit_formulas_titanic) %>% # dataframe a partir del objeto formulas
  mutate(models = names(logit_formulas_titanic), # columna con los nombres de las formulas
         expression = paste(logit_formulas_titanic), # columna con las expresiones de las formulas
         mod = map(logit_formulas_titanic, ~glm(.,family = 'binomial', data = na.omit(titanic.train))))

Genero un grafico para decidir el punto de corte

prediction_metrics <- function(cutoff, predictions=prediction_Edad.Clase.Sexo.Puerto){
  table <- predictions %>% 
    mutate(predicted_class=if_else(.fitted>cutoff, 1, 0) %>% as.factor(),
           Survived= factor(Survived))
  
  confusionMatrix(table$predicted_class,table$Survived, positive = "1") %>%
    tidy() %>%
    select(term, estimate) %>%
    filter(term %in% c('accuracy', 'sensitivity', 'specificity', 'precision','recall')) %>%
    mutate(cutoff=cutoff)
  }

cutoffs = seq(0.01,0.95,0.01)



logit_pred= map_dfr(cutoffs, prediction_metrics)%>% mutate(term=as.factor(term))
## Warning in confusionMatrix.default(table$predicted_class, table$Survived, :
## Levels are not in the same order for reference and data. Refactoring data
## to match.
ggplot(logit_pred, aes(cutoff,estimate, group=term, color=term)) + geom_line(size=1) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(title= 'Accuracy, Sensitivity, Specificity, Recall y Precision', subtitle= 'Modelo completo', color="")

Busco el punto de corte con el mayor accuracy

logit_pred %>% filter(term=="accuracy") %>% filter(estimate==max(estimate))
